Repository Name Unauthorized: University of Florida Department of Special & Area Studies Collections  George A. Smathers Libraries
Notes: The Department is well know for its Floridiana, the papers of Florida authors and politicians. There is also a performing arts collection, mainly 60,000 items of primary source ephemera from 19th and 20th Century Europe and America, and the Samuel Proctor Oral History Program an extensive oral history collection with containing 5,000 interviews and 85,000 pages of transcripts.  Refer to website for details of holdings.
